[
    {
        "content": "<p>As part of my effort to make the x86 boot path more generic and more idiomatic, ELF based etc, I am trying to switch to the 'small' code model for the core kernel when CONFIG_RELOCATABLE=y. This allows the kernel to be linked as a PIE executable, like other sane architectures do, rather than rely on dodgy hacks to perform runtime relocation on a position dependent binary. The ultimate goal here is to allow things like fgkaslr (fine grained kaslr) to be designed/implemented only once, in the ELF domain, and be deployed across architectures.</p>\n<p>Currently, when building with -Ccode-model=small, I get an error like</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">error</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">unused</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">import</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"k\">super</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">bindings_helper</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"err\">`</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"p\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">usr</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">local</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">google</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">home</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">ardb</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">linux</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">rust</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">bindings</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">lib</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">rs</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"mi\">49</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"mi\">13</span>\n<span class=\"w\">   </span><span class=\"o\">|</span>\n<span class=\"mi\">49</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\">     </span><span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">use</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">super</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">bindings_helper</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">   </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\">             </span><span class=\"o\">^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^</span>\n<span class=\"w\">   </span><span class=\"o\">|</span>\n<span class=\"w\">   </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">note</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">D</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">unused</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">imports</span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">implied</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">by</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">D</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">warnings</span><span class=\"err\">`</span>\n<span class=\"w\">   </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">help</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">to</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kr\">override</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">D</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">warnings</span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">add</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"cp\">#[allow(unused_imports)]</span><span class=\"err\">`</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">error</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">unused</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">import</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"k\">super</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">bindings_raw</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"err\">`</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"p\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">usr</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">local</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">google</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">home</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">ardb</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">linux</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">rust</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">bindings</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">lib</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">rs</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"mi\">62</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"mi\">9</span>\n<span class=\"w\">   </span><span class=\"o\">|</span>\n<span class=\"mi\">62</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\">     </span><span class=\"k\">use</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">super</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">bindings_raw</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">   </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\">         </span><span class=\"o\">^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">error</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">aborting</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">due</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">to</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">previous</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">errors</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">make</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"p\">]:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">***</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">usr</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">local</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">google</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">home</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">ardb</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">linux</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">rust</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">Makefile</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"mi\">669</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">rust</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">bindings</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">o</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Error</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>which makes me suspect that perhaps other kernel-related rustc behavior has been made dependent on the code model? Or is something else going wrong here?</p>\n<p>Adding -Ccode-model=small to KBUILD_RUSTFLAGS_KERNEL should be sufficient to reproduce this (based on v6.19-rc1)</p>",
        "id": 565423029,
        "sender_full_name": "Ard Biesheuvel",
        "timestamp": 1766739240
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Actually, the issue seems to be the visibility #pragma in include/linux/hidden.h being visible to bindgen, and this is easily fixed.</p>\n<p>Next question is whether rustc has the notion of -fdirect-access-external-data, to avoid GOT indirections, which are never needed in a fully linked binary such as vmlinux.</p>",
        "id": 565425255,
        "sender_full_name": "Ard Biesheuvel",
        "timestamp": 1766740984
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>There's an <code>-Zdirect-access-external-data</code> flag</p>",
        "id": 565430586,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1766745575
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"519727\">Alice Ryhl</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/288089-General/topic/Builtin.20Rust.20components.20fail.20to.20build.20with.20small.20code.20model/near/565430586\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>There's an <code>-Zdirect-access-external-data</code> flag</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>That seems to work, thanks!</p>",
        "id": 565430918,
        "sender_full_name": "Ard Biesheuvel",
        "timestamp": 1766745807
    },
    {
        "content": "<blockquote>\n<p>There's an <code>-Zdirect-access-external-data</code> flag</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Indeed, WANG Rui of LoongArch implemented it in upstream Rust a while ago and it is already used in Linux for that arch (no minimum needed, added in 1.78).</p>",
        "id": 565564963,
        "sender_full_name": "Miguel Ojeda",
        "timestamp": 1766923274
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I feel like this should be a new <code>relocation-model</code> rather than an ad-hoc flag.</p>",
        "id": 565584352,
        "sender_full_name": "Gary Guo",
        "timestamp": 1766947996
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Maybe suggest it on zulip?</p>",
        "id": 565584523,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1766948256
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>the other one, I mean</p>",
        "id": 565584527,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1766948267
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>You mean rust-for-linux channel in rust zulip?</p>",
        "id": 565584814,
        "sender_full_name": "Gary Guo",
        "timestamp": 1766948497
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"413824\">Gary Guo</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/288089-General/topic/Builtin.20Rust.20components.20fail.20to.20build.20with.20small.20code.20model/near/565584352\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I feel like this should be a new <code>relocation-model</code> rather than an ad-hoc flag.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Agreed, and this has come up in the past for the C side of the kernel too, but we never got anywhere. Something like <code>-fstatic-pie</code> would be useful to convey that the executable needs to be relocatable at load time, but does not use shared objects. Unfortunately, in the ELF world, things like symbol preemption, dynamic loading and minimizing the CoW footprint of an executable are all piled together.</p>\n<p>So yes, something like <code>-Crelocation-model=static-pie</code> which results in PIC codegen but no GOT indirections would be useful too. Only potential problem are weak references, but does Rust even support those?</p>",
        "id": 565585057,
        "sender_full_name": "Ard Biesheuvel",
        "timestamp": 1766948947
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Weak references occassionaly come up when discussing how to implement certain potential new features, but it's not used by any features today.</p>",
        "id": 565585123,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1766949065
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Posted in rust-lang zulip: <a href=\"https://rust-lang.zulipchat.com/#narrow/channel/425075-rust-for-linux/topic/New.20relocation.20model.20for.20relocatable.20code.20but.20static.20data/with/565584971\">https://rust-lang.zulipchat.com/#narrow/channel/425075-rust-for-linux/topic/New.20relocation.20model.20for.20relocatable.20code.20but.20static.20data/with/565584971</a></p>",
        "id": 565585287,
        "sender_full_name": "Gary Guo",
        "timestamp": 1766949366
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Linked both in <a href=\"https://github.com/Rust-for-Linux/linux/issues/2\">#2</a>.</p>",
        "id": 565585693,
        "sender_full_name": "Miguel Ojeda",
        "timestamp": 1766950142
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Note that arm64 already depends on this behavior, but <code>-Crelocation-model=static</code> happens to produce code that is position independent, and -fpie produces GOT based symbol references (using ADRP/LDR) that can always be relaxed into direct references (using ADRP/ADD). On x86, any memory operand could be a GOT slot, and so relaxations are not always possible,</p>",
        "id": 565594503,
        "sender_full_name": "Ard Biesheuvel",
        "timestamp": 1766954597
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>BTW it looks like GCC (and clang) does have <code>-static-pie</code>? How is different from <code>direct-access-external-data</code>?</p>",
        "id": 566050424,
        "sender_full_name": "Gary Guo",
        "timestamp": 1767355208
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Does <a href=\"https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/149622\">rust#149622 Change <code>aarch64-unknown-none</code> to generate static-PIE binaries by default</a> matter for us in relation to this topic?</p>",
        "id": 566059073,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1767361148
    }
]